Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Mix flour, baking soda and salt until well blended; set aside. Beat margarine and sugars in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla; mix well. Gradually add flour mixture, beating well after each addition. Stir in chocolate and walnuts. Drop heaping tablespoonfuls of dough, 2 inches apart, onto baking sheets. Bake 11 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool 1 minute; remove to wire racks. Cool completely.